What is your understanding of DevOps and Cloud Engineering?
=> My understanding of Devops and cloude engineering is that it involves an engineer who manages all the backend components—such as server configuration, database configuration, and related infrastructure— that supports an applicationdelivered to end users across multiple platforms.

Why you are starting learning DevOps & Cloud?
=> I am a Java developer, and I want to upskill myself to better understand what happens behind the scenes. I am also eager to transition into a DevOps role.

Where do you want to reach?
=> 1) short term goal: I want to learn not only the theory but also gain hands-on(CI/CD, Skripting(git cicd, jenkins)) experience by the end of this course.
2) long term goal: I aim to transition into a DevOps role.

How you will stay consistent every single day?
=> As a working professional, I can dedicate 1–1.5 hours every day and 5–6 hours on weekends. I am highly motivated and confident that I will use this time effectively. Even if I have just one hour, it will be focused and productive.
